## Change 3: Add \\NoPath\\ Pattern Documentation

**Insert after line 270 (Configuration File Support section):**

```markdown
### Optional File Paths with \\NoPath\\

When a configuration file is not required or not available, use the `\\NoPath\\` sentinel value:

**Pattern:**
```polyglot
[w] |W.Runtime.Python3.11
(|) <requirements:pg.path << \\NoPath\\  // ‚Üź No requirements file
(|) >env:pg.serial >> $py
```

**When to use:**
- Configuration file is optional
- Running without external dependencies
- Embedded/inline configuration instead of file-based

**Example:**
```polyglot
// With requirements file
[w] |W.Runtime.Python3.11
(|) <requirements:pg.path << |Path"/config/requirements.txt"
(|) >env:pg.serial >> $py

// Without requirements file
[w] |W.Runtime.Python3.11
(|) <requirements:pg.path << \\NoPath\\
(|) >env:pg.serial >> $py
```

**Note:** `\\NoPath\\` is a special sentinel value, not a string. It signals the runtime wrapper to skip file loading.

---
```

