### 5. Use kwargs for Python Function Arguments

Always use the `<kwargs.*` pattern for named arguments:

```polyglot
‚úÖ Good:
(|) <kwargs.param_name:type << $value

‚ĚĆ Avoid: Positional arguments (not supported)
```

### 6. Use \\NoPath\\ for Optional Files

When configuration files are not needed:

```polyglot
‚úÖ Good:
(|) <requirements:pg.path << \\NoPath\\

‚ĚĆ Avoid: Empty string
(|) <requirements:pg.path << ""
```

